snippet.textDisplay:
The big chunky screwdriver is the Mahi. The little one that comes in the Pro Tech kit is Mako. Both in one kit is Manta. I have both the Mako (via Pro Tech) and the Mahi, and I love them both.

The thing a lot of people complain about with the Mahi is that it's magnetic enough to hold the bits, but not so magnetic that it also holds screws very well. That's desirable when working on seriously vintage machines around e.g. floppy disks. I love both driver sets.

snippet.textDisplay: A Ghost S1 with 2 large tophats is slightly less volume than this and fits 2 x 240mm radiators instead of 1 x 280mm. I know there's someone making a Ghost/Dancase style sandwich layout case with an integrated distro plate, but if someone could make it vertical with the I/O on the bottom like this case it would be perfect. That way you could have a smaller footprint, and a bit less recirculating of hot air exhausted from the bottom.
